						               													<description>Hardcoded is a simultaneous action-selection fighting game, where players secretly program their characters to perform special moves in an attempt to outmaneuver and ultimately knock out their opponents. The game can be played free-for-all (2, 3, or 4 players), in teams of 2 (4 players), or against an AI opponent.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game is played in rounds. Each round consists of several parts:&amp;#10;1. roll for speed (simultaneous, secret);&amp;#10;2. select actions (simultaneous, secret);&amp;#10;3. reveal actions;&amp;#10;4. player turns (each player in speed order move on the board and attack if possible);&amp;#10;5. pass priority tracker and start the next round.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each character starts with 5 HP. When a character is dealt damage, their HP is reduced by that amount. A character reduced to 0 HP is Knocked Out (KO&amp;rsquo;d). A KO&amp;rsquo;d character respawns at the end of the current round. The player that KO&amp;rsquo;d them receives 1 point, and the first player (or team) to reach 2 points wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
